{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9ce29b6-8981-474f-9839-bdbce54e309a","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update packages** — replace the runner:\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n**2. Upgrade xUnit to v3** — MTP requires xUnit v3:\n```xml\n<!-- Replace xunit 2.9.3 with: -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n**3. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**4. Run tests** with:\n```bash\ndotnet test\n# or run the test project directly:\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- xUnit v3 has some API changes from v2 (e.g., `Assert.Equal` for collections is stricter, `TheoryData` is generic). Review the [xUnit v3 migration guide](https://xunit.net/docs/v3-migration).\n- MTP makes your test project a standalone executable — hence `OutputType` = `Exe`.\n- If you use `Trait`, `MemberData`, etc., they still work but double-check for namespace changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f64367e-3290-48a8-8494-93bacdc05ae2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"4C1D:30490E:D03DDD:103E4FC:6A0128B7"},"id":"acd8c2a7-f495-4e35-b621-de5825d62bbc","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:25.751Z","parentId":"5fa4fe4c-2986-42cf-b381-e5c701f711fd"}
